I don't know if I should put this with the likes of Nintendo's Mario games in the platformer section but at the same time I feel like it deserves it. This original platformer for the iOS operating system is just what we needed. It's controls work almost too perfectly as a mobile game. You swipe to make your dog grow. You can use this in unique ways to get to the next dog house. This game is challenging and fun. Not only is it the first platformer I have seen on iOS but I have a feeling it's going to be the best no matter what other platformers are on here. If you're reading this, do yourself a favor and download this game right. Now. Also for all you people who are concerned about the music, it's pretty good for a platformer game. One last thing, this game doesn't have that many ads and they aren't as intrusive as you'd think for a game like this. So don't worry about ads. Other than it not being ad-free this is a game truly worthy of a 5/5. I wish the developers luck and hope they proceed to make an even more brilliant game.

This game is great for the same reason the NES and Gameboy-era games it mimics were great: It commits to a single core game mechanic (stretching your dog to ridiculous lengths, around corners, etc.) and sticks with it to the end.  The game remains fun and fresh throughout without ever introducing new mechanics by constantly finding new ways to exercise the one you already know.  And when you finally clear the game?  It's an awesome feeling.
